<sect1 id="s1-satellite-hostname" os="hidden">
    <title>Changing the &susemgr; Hostname</title>
    <remark>taroth 2011-02-11: disabled for now, see https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=671191</remark>    
    <remark>ke 2011-05-22: still not available, see https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=695357</remark>
    
    <para>
        If you need to change the hostname or IP address of the &susemgr; server,
        the <filename>spacewalk-utils</filename> package contains the
        <filename>spacewalk-hostname-rename</filename> script.
    </para>
    
    <remark>mdejmek: what is this step for? redundant, right?</remark>
    
    <para>
        To use the <command>spacewalk-hostname-rename</command> script, you must
        first ensure that you know your SSL CA passphrase by performing the
        following command:
    </para>
    
    <remark condition="clarity">
        2011-02-03 - fs: RHN-ORG-PRIVATE-SSL-KEY: Correct filename?
    </remark>
    
    <screen>openssl rsa -in <replaceable>path</replaceable>/RHN-ORG-PRIVATE-SSL-KEY
</screen>
    
    <para>
        Enter the passphrase when prompted.
    </para>
    
    <para>
        <command>spacewalk-hostname-rename</command> requires one mandatory
        argument, which is the IP address of the &susemgr; server, regardless of
        whether the IP address will change along with the hostname or not.
    </para>
    
    <para>
        The usage of <command>spacewalk-hostname-rename</command> is:
    </para>
    
    <screen>spacewalk-hostname-rename &lt;ip address&gt; [ --ssl-country=&lt;country&gt; \
--ssl-state=&lt;state&gt; --ssl-org=&lt;organization/company&gt;\
--ssl-orgunit=&lt;department&gt; --ssl-email=&lt;email address&gt; \
--ssl-ca-password=&lt;password&gt;]</screen>
    
    <para>
        Changing the hostname requires a new SSL certificate. If not all
        necessary options are passed at the command-line (as in the above
        example), they will be asked interactively.
    </para>
    
